00:22:39,606 --> 00:22:46,289
The choice to do a 2D game came naturally. I was a big fan of Karateka on Apple 2,

254
00:22:47,289 --> 00:22:54,473
and that was a kind of game I felt comfortable to create, so I went this way.

255
00:22:56,094 --> 00:22:57,574
So, what's the player doing?

256
00:22:59,335 --> 00:23:02,377
All gameplay activity is very traditional in many aspects.

257
00:23:03,077 --> 00:23:05,758
You fight, you run, you jump, you flee, you die.

258
00:23:07,385 --> 00:23:15,170
But the environment suggests a narrative and gives more meaning to these basic actions.

259
00:23:21,033 --> 00:23:29,297
The color palette. Only 16 in total and it was very difficult to define.

