00:23:29,317 --> 00:23:36,021
A whole week was needed to define the first color palette.

261
00:23:37,085 --> 00:23:43,530
full one week full time for 16 colors, a determining choice for the atmosphere of the game.

262
00:23:45,491 --> 00:23:54,377
Some colors are sometimes used both for the landscape and for the character. For instance,

263
00:23:55,738 --> 00:24:02,242
the hero's flesh color was also used to suggest the sunset reflected on the rock.

264
00:24:06,093 --> 00:24:08,875
Having only 16 colors is very restrictive.

265
00:24:09,355 --> 00:24:11,696
You could understand my need to optimize

266
00:24:11,776 --> 00:24:15,397
the use of each color as each hue had multiple uses.

267
00:24:16,778 --> 00:24:20,160
Giving Lester dark hair would have been an easy solution.

268
00:24:21,120 --> 00:24:24,641
But I didn't want him to look too much like me.

269
00:24:26,202 --> 00:24:29,784
Yes, because I was filming myself to create animation.

270
00:24:30,664 --> 00:24:33,565
And the hero was physically nearly identical to me.

271
00:24:33,905 --> 00:24:34,966
It was disturbing.

272
00:24:37,343 --> 00:24:42,005
So I didn't want to see myself running on the screen,

273
00:24:42,325 --> 00:24:45,586
being killed by a slug or whatever.

274
00:24:47,287 --> 00:24:52,429
So I decided to choose a totally different color, red,

275
00:24:53,670 --> 00:24:55,751
because I was sure that this color would be

276
00:24:55,791 --> 00:24:57,591
very useful in many pictures.

277
00:24:58,232 --> 00:25:02,874
And I also wanted Lester to stand out

278
00:25:03,114 --> 00:25:03,914
from the background.

279
00:25:07,379 --> 00:25:10,022
and I will never have red hair.

280
00:25:12,263 --> 00:25:13,665
Only blue hair sometime.

281
00:25:21,131 --> 00:25:28,638
So, during the creation of this part, I defined the vocabulary used through the whole game.

282
00:25:29,579 --> 00:25:30,600
We will see this right now.

283
00:25:34,110 --> 00:25:39,014
Creating a 2D game limits the gameplay to one plane,

284
00:25:39,694 --> 00:25:43,797
but it gives the advantage of exploiting more freely

285
00:25:44,598 --> 00:25:48,981
the depth at the front and the back of the scene

286
00:25:49,081 --> 00:25:49,821
for something else.

287
00:25:53,064 --> 00:25:56,206
This in order to build narrative without interrupting

288
00:25:56,346 --> 00:25:57,287
player activity.

289
00:25:59,668 --> 00:26:02,530
Here, the black beast can be seen from the beginning.

290
00:26:03,482 --> 00:26:05,964
so the player can start to think about it.

291
00:26:08,746 --> 00:26:13,650
So it's really a suggestion of a story.

292
00:26:18,053 --> 00:26:22,677
And what happens in the background suddenly becomes real for the player.

