00:32:11,559 --> 00:32:13,800
And we have this.

341
00:32:27,520 --> 00:32:31,423
In retrospect, this is one aspect I'm very proud of,

342
00:32:31,463 --> 00:32:35,505
because the player has to choose from different strategies.

343
00:32:36,005 --> 00:32:38,967
The player can use a small shot immediately,

344
00:32:39,447 --> 00:32:44,350
but without protection, or risk his life creating a shield,

345
00:32:44,830 --> 00:32:48,172
and ultimately, even taking more time

346
00:32:48,232 --> 00:32:52,455
to create plasma to destroy enemy shields or doors.

347
00:32:54,008 --> 00:32:57,611
So somehow, this became the building blocks

348
00:32:57,771 --> 00:32:59,732
to different types of gameplay.

349
00:33:01,854 --> 00:33:04,376
After designing my weaponry, I needed

350
00:33:04,476 --> 00:33:08,480
to develop exploratory notions.

351
00:33:09,400 --> 00:33:13,544
Everything up to this point was on a single level.

352
00:33:16,006 --> 00:33:17,447
On a single level on the screen, I mean.

353
00:33:18,888 --> 00:33:20,389
But I felt limited.

354
00:33:21,950 --> 00:33:23,291
Having several stages.

355
00:33:23,987 --> 00:33:27,169
in a game screen would bring more tactics and puzzles.

356
00:33:28,949 --> 00:33:32,171
But the difficulty was to create character animation

357
00:33:32,391 --> 00:33:34,191
and collision on stairs.

358
00:33:35,272 --> 00:33:37,653
How could I do this with little effort?

359
00:33:38,033 --> 00:33:40,594
I was thinking of a real elevator,

360
00:33:41,014 --> 00:33:42,355
but another idea came.

361
00:33:42,675 --> 00:33:44,896
Why not create a kind of teleporter

362
00:33:45,416 --> 00:33:49,558
to switch from level to level just

363
00:33:49,638 --> 00:33:52,439
by drawing a few vertical polygons?

364
00:33:53,767 --> 00:33:59,791
in Lester's color, I realized that I could create a very nice impression of motion.

365
00:34:00,591 --> 00:34:02,132
Something that was inspired by

