00:34:33,922 --> 00:34:39,824
At this point, I realized that I couldn't let him go without finding him again.

370
00:34:40,484 --> 00:34:42,244
I felt attached to him.

371
00:34:47,446 --> 00:34:51,907
Okay, I only did one third of the game.

372
00:34:52,567 --> 00:34:53,608
And at this rhythm...

373
00:34:54,430 --> 00:35:00,075
I would have two more years of work, which was really depressing.

374
00:35:01,976 --> 00:35:08,341
From that point, I decided to work more and to not get lost in details.

375
00:35:11,404 --> 00:35:13,306
Some backgrounds were more flattened.

376
00:35:15,628 --> 00:35:22,854
So I got organized and created a set of graphic blocks I could reuse to create detailed

377
00:35:24,472 --> 00:35:25,712
backgrounds fastened.

378
00:35:38,534 --> 00:35:46,676
From that point, I focused more on puzzles, creating variations using the building blocks

379
00:35:47,256 --> 00:35:48,377
I had at my disposal.

380
00:35:50,817 --> 00:35:54,321
and each time I was trying to bring a new idea.

381
00:35:58,305 --> 00:36:00,408
The friend became the center of the story

382
00:36:01,028 --> 00:36:04,072
with a succession of twists

383
00:36:04,853 --> 00:36:07,456
where Lester and his friend helped each other.

384
00:36:30,993 --> 00:36:37,175
I never wanted at the beginning to create a game about the relationship between two strangers,

385
00:36:37,576 --> 00:36:40,937
but the improvisation led me naturally to this.

386
00:36:41,577 --> 00:36:45,559
Producing is a source of inspiration in itself.

387
00:36:52,302 --> 00:36:57,084
Then I extended the use of parallel action to the foreground.

388
00:36:57,844 --> 00:36:58,064
Here?

389
00:36:59,417 --> 00:37:06,820
When the player leaves the jail, we can see the frame being chased by guards in the foreground.

390
00:37:09,741 --> 00:37:14,984
This has the same effect as a close-up, but without breaking the player's activity.

391
00:37:31,132 --> 00:37:37,557
On the first level, I discovered the pleasure of modulating the pacing.

392
00:37:38,557 --> 00:37:40,719
But now, I was playing around with it.

393
00:37:41,279 --> 00:37:49,705
For example, to modulate the pacing, I used laser beams to give different rhythms, enabling

394
00:37:49,745 --> 00:37:55,428
me to modulate the tension, a little bit like music score.

